External morphology (Fig. 31
A-D
). Body relatively narrow. Foot and tail moderate, anterior foot corners long. Oral tentacles long. Rhinophores ca. 1.5 times longer than oral tentacles, slightly wrinkled. Dorsal cerata finger-shaped to fusiform, forming several clusters along dorsal edges. Apices of cerata gradually pointed, with elongate cnidosac. Distinct notal edge remains mostly below cerata clusters. Digestive gland diverticulum fills significant volume of the cerata. Anal opening on right side below second large cluster cerata. Reproductive openings lateral, below first anterior cluster of cerata.
